
[1]hatchel

   HATCH'EL, n. An instrument formed with long iron teeth set in a board,
   for cleaning flax or hemp from the tow, hards or coarse part. The
   hatchel is a large species of comb.

   HATCH'EL, v.t. To draw flax or hemp through the teeth of a hatchel, for
   separating the coarse part and broken pieces of the stalk from the fine
   fibrous parts.

   1. To tease or vex, by sarcasms or reproaches; a vulgar use of the
   word.
